@node qdocs "Game docs"

@{b}MENUS@{ub}
@{b}-----@{ub}

@{b}Choosing level@{ub}

Just click 'choose level' button and choose a level.
If you want a randomlevel just click 'randomize' button.

@{b}Options menu@{ub}

In here you can change the game options...
(movetime, Field of vision, explosions, banzaibrains etc.)
and save them.

@{b}Teams menu@{ub}

In here you can clear team(make new team) and change
names of the players and the team.
you can also load/save teams.

@{b} Weapons menu@{ub}

Here you can buy your weapons to all 4 soldiers in the team.
your money and other info is shown in the lefthand corner.
Some weapons can only be bought by the Leader or sergeant. (read
description)

To change item click on the arrowbuttons or picture of an item.
(item name&prize will be shown at the bottom of the screen.)


@{b}Game Controls@{ub}
@{b}-------------@{ub}

The game is controlled via mouse and keyboard.

mouse              -> scroll view
left mouse button  -> target select (teleport,nuke,team placing)
right mouse button -> weapons menu

del                -> weapons menu
help               -> shows names & energy (help exits)
arrows             -> aim, move humanoid, change weapon in weapons menu
return             -> jump, pick a weapon (in toolsmenu)
spacebar           -> use item, choose power (bazookas, grenades etc.)
esc                -> abort game
n                  -> end turn



Basic in game info:

When you see green Z rotating in upper-right corner it means
that you'r in Zombie MODE. (and Zombie MODE means that you are NOT
allowed to do anything except move around.) (press n to end your turn)
@endnode

@node dev "Technical..."

developing tools:
- Blitz II (who said that basic sucks?)
- Devpack (best assembler around)
- Brilliance
- Octamed pro

About the code:
The code is 95% Basic & 5% assembler and it's not so fast as it could be.
(Blitz is pretty fast except the variable handling)

This game requires a fast machine and lots of mem.
First reason is the colours (256!) as blitting is slower
and 256 colour bitmap eats much more mem than 32 colour bitmap.
Second reason is that i have made this game using A1200 with
accelerator and i had no chance to test it on a slower machine.
@endnode

